This pretty much reminds me Fire Emblem, exept that you don't get a false ending, but just a death quote on the death of a character. You still have only one life, no continues, etc... (exept that you can sometimes continue the game if you wish even if not all characters are alive).<br /><br />Live a Live (SNES) also had a lot of False endings, each featuring "false credits".<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Wed Dec 05, 2007 1:16 pm</p><hr />
