<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3756&amp;p=29129#p29129"><![CDATA[
Imagine a video game where only half the ROM is filled with game play. The other half is entirely composed of <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NonstandardGameOver" class="postlink">false ending</a> cutscenes showing the ramifications of the player character's death, depending on where and how the character died. There are no extra lives. There are no continues. However, the player can start at any "episode".<br /><br />Has this been done?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 05, 2007 11:31 am</p><hr />
